SIMPLE: bipinnatifid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bipinnatifid
<hw>Bi`pin*nat"i*fid</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>pinnatifid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Doubly pinnatifid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>A <xex>bipinnatifid leaf</xex> is a pinnatifid leaf having its
segments or divisions also pinnatifid. The primary divisions are
pinn⟦ae⟧ and the secondary <xex>pinnules</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Biplane</ent>⟦br⟧
